1
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:28,050
The person in the painting

2
00:00:28,050 --> 00:00:30,110
is the woman my mentor loved the most.

3
00:00:31,390 --> 00:00:32,100
So it's you.

4
00:00:34,610 --> 00:00:35,670
What do you mean?

5
00:00:37,740 --> 00:00:38,780
What does that mean?

6
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:40,210
What exactly is the relationship

7
00:00:40,210 --> 00:00:41,170
between your mentor and mine?

8
00:00:41,170 --> 00:00:42,300
Explain it clearly.

9
00:00:42,650 --> 00:00:44,380
Actually, I'm not sure myself.

10
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:45,790
I only know that my mentor

11
00:00:47,110 --> 00:00:49,040
waited for someone his whole life.

12
00:00:50,290 --> 00:00:51,280
Since I entered the mountain,

13
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:52,210
my mentor told me

14
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:56,430
[Memorial Tablet
of Mentor Zhang Qianzhang]

15
00:00:53,030 --> 00:00:54,630
that his only mission in life

16
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,530
was to wait for a flare shot.

17
00:00:57,070 --> 00:00:58,470
Whoever fires the flare,

18
00:00:59,170 --> 00:01:00,280
my mentor must obey

19
00:01:00,470 --> 00:01:01,730
all of their commands.

20
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:04,300
But why did it take you so long?

21
00:01:05,430 --> 00:01:07,230
He waited for you his whole life.

22
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:08,990
I forgot.

23
00:01:10,950 --> 00:01:11,880
What did you say?

24
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,789
Y-Y-You forgot?

25
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:16,760
It's normal for you to be emotional now.

26
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:17,890
You're still young.

27
00:01:17,900 --> 00:01:19,500
But you'll understand later

28
00:01:19,510 --> 00:01:21,900
that being too attached
only moves yourself.

29
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:23,060
If your mentor was willing to wait,

30
00:01:23,060 --> 00:01:24,320
that was his business.

31
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:26,350
Everyone has their own path.

32
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,200
Let's talk business.

33
00:01:34,490 --> 00:01:36,509
How many things have you promised
others recklessly?

34
00:01:36,509 --> 00:01:38,340
Can you stop making reckless promises?

35
00:01:38,340 --> 00:01:40,009
Ordinary people have hard lives.

36
00:01:40,009 --> 00:01:41,280
They are not meant to play with you.

37
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:43,580
But I never promised him I'd come back.

38
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:45,850
And I didn't know he'd wait so long.

39
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,259
Little Taoist,

40
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,600
since you're the contact for the Archives,

41
00:01:56,210 --> 00:01:56,930
I have a question.

42
00:01:56,930 --> 00:01:58,660
Which one of you fire the flare?

43
00:01:59,140 --> 00:02:00,240
I only listen to that person.

44
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:00,820
-Me.
-Me.

45
00:02:03,140 --> 00:02:04,460
Why are you talking nonsense?

46
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:05,930
Why are you spouting nonsense?

47
00:02:05,930 --> 00:02:06,570
You are my mentor.

48
00:02:06,570 --> 00:02:07,540
Can't you be more tolerant?

49
00:02:07,540 --> 00:02:10,470
-Are you fighting me for it now?
-He shot it. He did it.

50
00:02:15,690 --> 00:02:17,690
Don't we need tokens to go to Bailejing?

51
00:02:17,690 --> 00:02:19,220
I heard they're hard to get.

52
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,660
-Do you—
-Come with me.

53
00:02:28,740 --> 00:02:29,440
These...

54
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,360
These

55
00:02:32,430 --> 00:02:34,490
are what my mentor collected for you.

56
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:36,750
He thought they'd be useful one day.

57
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:39,460
I didn't expect you
to be so untrustworthy.

58
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:43,720
If we go, I'll only take you.

59
00:02:43,810 --> 00:02:44,560
Not her.

60
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:47,120
If I don't go,

61
00:02:47,170 --> 00:02:48,150
he won't either.

62
00:02:51,130 --> 00:02:51,980
How about this?

63
00:02:51,980 --> 00:02:53,079
Give me 2 tokens,

64
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:54,560
and I'll go with my mentor.

65
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:56,870
The path to Bailejing is complex.

66
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:58,210
Without a guide,

67
00:02:58,210 --> 00:02:59,470
you can't get in at all.

68
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:02,440
If she goes, I won't.

69
00:03:02,740 --> 00:03:03,670
Then no one will.

70
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,380
Then I won't go.

71
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,310
You two go.

72
00:03:15,220 --> 00:03:16,600
Little Taoist.

73
00:03:17,860 --> 00:03:19,300
My mentor is sick.

74
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,960
I brought her to Bailejing

75
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:23,190
to seek treatment
from the chief of the Zhang family.

76
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:23,990
Why did you...

77
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:27,630
Look at you.

78
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:29,130
My mentor is really dying.

79
00:03:29,130 --> 00:03:30,090
If my mentor dies,

80
00:03:30,090 --> 00:03:31,130
and you don't save her,

81
00:03:31,130 --> 00:03:32,560
you'd be leaving her to die.

82
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,360
Would your conscience be clear?

83
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:40,680
Then...

84
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:44,020
then I'll go with you two.

85
00:03:44,130 --> 00:03:45,260
For no other reason,

86
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,960
I just want to see

87
00:03:47,180 --> 00:03:48,840
what the woman my mentor loved

88
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:50,160
is really like.

89
00:03:52,970 --> 00:03:54,130
Have you been to Bailejing?

90
00:03:54,130 --> 00:03:55,130
Of course, I have.

91
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:01,700
Wait.

92
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:04,190
Why are you both so arrogant?

93
00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:48,270
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

94
00:05:48,690 --> 00:05:51,250
[Episode 25]

95
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:32,159
[Nanqiang to Changxiang]

96
00:06:52,510 --> 00:06:53,310
Come out.

97
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,330
Let's talk.

98
00:07:12,420 --> 00:07:13,220
About what?

99
00:07:13,810 --> 00:07:15,010
Zhang Haixia.

100
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:17,370
Zhang Haixia is in Mo Yungao's team.

101
00:07:17,370 --> 00:07:18,640
Stop joking, will you?

102
00:07:20,310 --> 00:07:21,420
Am I joking?

103
00:07:24,180 --> 00:07:25,180
Isn't that perfect?

104
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:27,440
Saves you the trouble of looking for him.

105
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:33,360
You two didn't hide anything else
from me before?

106
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,250
Like what?

107
00:07:41,810 --> 00:07:43,340
Didn't he say anything else

108
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:44,930
to you before?

109
00:07:47,180 --> 00:07:48,040
No.

110
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,960
I actually want to ask you

111
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:52,360
if you know something.

112
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:54,610
I've told you everything I know.

113
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:04,020
Shrimpie must have his reasons.

114
00:08:05,450 --> 00:08:06,890
It's quite unusual for Mo Yungao

115
00:08:06,890 --> 00:08:08,690
to suddenly appear in Nanqiang.

116
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,640
Do you think Shrimpie
did those abnormal things

117
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:14,310
just to get close to Mo Yungao?

118
00:08:15,130 --> 00:08:16,070
If you want to find him,

119
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:17,300
go now.

120
00:08:17,390 --> 00:08:18,990
Leave me in peace for a while.

121
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,060
Forget it.

122
00:08:30,020 --> 00:08:31,480
He might have his reasons,

123
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,330
but you are really going to die.

124
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:36,870
I'm not the same as before.

125
00:08:36,870 --> 00:08:38,530
I know what's more important.

126
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:41,090
Let's find the chief to cure you first.

127
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:43,049
We'll solve his problem later.

128
00:08:45,370 --> 00:08:46,550
Mo Yungao has such a large team.

129
00:08:46,550 --> 00:08:47,750
He'll be easy to find.

130
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:54,920
Then let me ask you,

131
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,650
if he really did something

132
00:08:56,650 --> 00:08:58,020
unforgivable,

133
00:08:58,770 --> 00:08:59,770
what would you do?

134
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,230
Pretend it never happened.

135
00:09:14,890 --> 00:09:15,670
Then clean up his mess

136
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:16,670
and take him home.

137
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,260
Just like he did for me before.

138
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,900
It's late. Stop drinking.

139
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:32,160
We have to hit the road tomorrow.

140
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:11,680
[Routine inspection of flare shots]

141
00:10:18,910 --> 00:10:21,440
[Zhang Qianzhang, the Zhang family's
contact in Nanqiang]

142
00:10:39,410 --> 00:10:45,210
♪ The past fades into traces on the page ♪

143
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:52,210
♪ A silent breeze
brushes past that lingering warmth ♪

144
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:59,470
♪ In this fleeting world,
I long for a moment of vivid life ♪

145
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:05,190
♪ I may have a chance to open a door ♪

146
00:11:06,690 --> 00:11:13,160
♪ Where love and wish
meet in a fleeting moment ♪

147
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:20,110
♪ There's no need to ask questions
in the maze ♪

148
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:23,090
♪ The world's bustle ♪

149
00:11:23,670 --> 00:11:28,580
♪ Can briefly warm
those under a shared roof ♪

150
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:35,350
♪ And the story has come to an end ♪

151
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:33,890
[Four months later]

152
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,420
Will you come back?

153
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,080
If I do,

154
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,010
I'll let you know with a flare shot.

155
00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:53,730
♪ Clouds drift and fade just a few years ♪

156
00:11:57,710 --> 00:12:00,470
♪ Mortal world grass
regrows after parting ♪

157
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:12,430
♪ Truth or lie, seasons pass
in fleeting years ♪

158
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:09,000
Come on, get up quickly.

159
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,200
From now on,

160
00:12:13,410 --> 00:12:19,420
♪ A silent breeze
brushes past that lingering warmth ♪

161
00:12:13,610 --> 00:12:16,310
[Young Zhang Qianjunwanma]

162
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:16,100
you are my beloved disciple.

163
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:18,360
Your only mission in this life

164
00:12:19,210 --> 00:12:21,260
is to wait for a flare shot.

165
00:12:20,690 --> 00:12:26,670
♪ In this fleeting world,
I long for a moment of vivid life ♪

166
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:24,060
Whoever fires the flare,

167
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:26,600
you must fulfill

168
00:12:27,410 --> 00:12:28,840
whatever request they make.

169
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:32,400
♪ I may have a chance to open a door ♪

170
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:40,130
♪ Where love and wish
meet in a fleeting moment ♪

171
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:47,120
♪ There's no need to ask questions
in the maze ♪

172
00:12:47,930 --> 00:12:50,170
♪ The world's bustle ♪

173
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:55,790
♪ Can briefly warm
those under a shared roof ♪

174
00:12:56,770 --> 00:13:02,050
♪ And the story has come to an end ♪

175
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:01,580
Mentor,

176
00:13:02,270 --> 00:13:03,650
this year marks your 60th year of waiting

177
00:13:03,090 --> 00:13:09,670
♪ Gifted to us the luck to walk
side by side a stretch of way ♪

178
00:13:03,650 --> 00:13:05,160
in this mountain forest.

179
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,620
I've always wanted to ask you,

180
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,750
how can you wait your whole life

181
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:16,420
♪ After partings and meetings,
spring breeze comes round tomorrow ♪

182
00:13:11,270 --> 00:13:13,150
for something that seems

183
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:14,620
so illusory?

184
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:19,380
♪ The world's bustle ♪

185
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:25,250
♪ Can keep whose dream under the roof? ♪

186
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:21,030
I'm here.

187
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:25,030
What can make me wait for a lifetime

188
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:36,580
♪ No farewell wishes needed in this life ♪

189
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:29,860
is never an arrow.

190
00:13:33,390 --> 00:13:34,250
Then what is it?

191
00:13:34,670 --> 00:13:36,030
I'm thirsty.

192
00:13:36,460 --> 00:13:37,920
I'll go get you some water.

193
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:43,820
So,

194
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:50,030
she really isn't coming back.

195
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:26,300
I no longer want to wait for
other people's signal.

196
00:14:26,340 --> 00:14:28,270
I want to become the signal myself.

197
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:33,020
[Memorial Tablet
of Mentor Zhang Qianzhang]

198
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,150
I'll come back to see you.

199
00:14:40,350 --> 00:14:41,610
[Nanqiang to Changxiang]

200
00:15:01,450 --> 00:15:08,410
[Nanqiang to Changxiang]

201
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:19,370
Deep inside Nanqiang,

202
00:15:19,370 --> 00:15:20,480
there are Six Great Fortresses.

203
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:21,980
The outermost one is called Jinyadong,

204
00:15:21,980 --> 00:15:23,320
also known as Bailejing.

205
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,480
Jinyadong is the only place

206
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:26,910
where Nanqiang people
and outsiders live together.

207
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:27,970
During festivals,

208
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:29,480
they coat their teeth with gold powder

209
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:31,200
and then gather on the streets.

210
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,260
They're that rich?

211
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:33,670
How did they make their fortune?

212
00:15:33,670 --> 00:15:35,440
There is a river inside Bailejing.

213
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:36,720
One side leads to Jinzhou,

214
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:39,250
and the other side
leads to the Hongfen River.

215
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,320
It's a freight path
along the ancient Tea-Mule Trail,

216
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:42,170
leading to the Central Plains.

217
00:15:42,270 --> 00:15:43,930
That's why it's so rich there.

218
00:15:44,220 --> 00:15:46,330
At night, it's brightly lit

219
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,550
and bustling with people.

220
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:49,960
From a distance,
it looks like a galaxy in the mountains.

221
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:50,890
It's beautiful.

222
00:16:01,410 --> 00:16:02,670
Halt. Show your token.

223
00:16:12,630 --> 00:16:13,660
[Bailejing]

224
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:13,790
It's fake?

225
00:17:06,170 --> 00:17:06,960
Let's go in.

226
00:17:08,430 --> 00:17:10,160
Finally, something reliable.

227
00:17:33,220 --> 00:17:37,420
[Bailejing]

228
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,210
Zhang Qianjun,

229
00:17:56,940 --> 00:17:58,000
are you sure

230
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,700
you're leading us the right way?

231
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:01,220
This is different from what you said.

232
00:18:01,220 --> 00:18:02,650
Yeah, this is Bailejing.

233
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,400
Isn't it written on the sign?

234
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:07,180
I was dragged around for half a month

235
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:08,330
just to see this?

236
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:10,350
You know I don't have
many days left to live, right?

237
00:18:10,350 --> 00:18:11,810
When exactly did you come?

238
00:18:12,180 --> 00:18:12,790
In your past life?

239
00:18:12,790 --> 00:18:13,720
When I was young,

240
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:16,330
my mentor brought me here a few times.

241
00:18:16,330 --> 00:18:17,850
But it's been a while.

242
00:18:24,610 --> 00:18:26,010
[Happiness after Death]

243
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:26,140
Right, right.

244
00:18:27,050 --> 00:18:27,980
That's the place

245
00:18:28,330 --> 00:18:30,730
where my mentor
brought me to eat last time.

246
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:32,500
[Ancient Qiang Texts]
[Happiness after Death]

247
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:34,610
Is there any food?

248
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:37,500
Sir?

249
00:18:38,180 --> 00:18:38,920
I'll do it.

250
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:58,250
We got customers.

251
00:18:58,750 --> 00:18:59,310
Order.

252
00:19:01,570 --> 00:19:02,230
Okay, okay.

253
00:19:09,670 --> 00:19:11,800
What would the three of you like to eat?

254
00:19:12,270 --> 00:19:13,270
Give us some specials.

255
00:19:13,270 --> 00:19:14,110
Okay, okay.

256
00:19:15,270 --> 00:19:15,850
Hurry up.

257
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:16,560
Okay, okay.

258
00:19:21,070 --> 00:19:22,330
All dishes are served.

259
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:29,830
You really haven't eaten
anything good, have you?

260
00:19:29,830 --> 00:19:32,400
Sir, is this really Bailejing?

261
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:34,320
Bailejing, Jinglebai,

262
00:19:34,460 --> 00:19:36,860
call it whatever you like.
Enjoy your meal.

263
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:42,370
I think everyone here's not all there.

264
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:44,580
The chief is definitely not here.

265
00:19:45,110 --> 00:19:46,440
Don't eat these either.

266
00:19:47,110 --> 00:19:48,140
Let's discuss

267
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:49,480
how to find the chief.

268
00:19:49,550 --> 00:19:51,810
I don't know what the chief looks like.

269
00:19:52,070 --> 00:19:54,130
But I can take you to find him.

270
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:57,510
Follow me.

271
00:20:05,030 --> 00:20:05,630
Mentor.

272
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:07,100
The wind and waves are strong here.

273
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:08,810
Is he out of his mind too?

274
00:20:12,070 --> 00:20:12,930
Where are they?

275
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:16,900
What's wrong with you two?

276
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:20,550
Well...

277
00:20:23,530 --> 00:20:25,330
Why is there a little chick here?

278
00:20:29,610 --> 00:20:31,100
This chick is quite cute.

279
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:32,530
This chick is so cute.

280
00:20:51,640 --> 00:20:52,420
Hurry up,

281
00:20:52,810 --> 00:20:54,060
we're almost there!

282
00:20:54,510 --> 00:20:56,240
-Hurry up!
-The food is useful.

283
00:21:00,220 --> 00:21:00,680
Open your mouth.

284
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:01,830
Follow me!

285
00:21:05,910 --> 00:21:06,500
Mentor.

286
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:22,360
Do you feel much better?

287
00:21:26,310 --> 00:21:27,110
What's wrong?

288
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:43,500
Outsiders can't eat

289
00:21:43,580 --> 00:21:45,200
the food of Bailejing.

290
00:21:45,420 --> 00:21:46,530
One bite,

291
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:49,680
and you're dead.

292
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:54,140
What do you mean?

293
00:21:54,170 --> 00:21:55,610
It means once you eat it,

294
00:21:56,110 --> 00:21:57,880
there is no turning back.

295
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,690
Only after death can you

296
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:02,750
become a true Bailejing person.

297
00:22:02,770 --> 00:22:04,240
True Bailejing people!

298
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:07,820
You won't die.

299
00:22:08,450 --> 00:22:10,130
Everyone has to die!

300
00:22:11,450 --> 00:22:12,850
I'll take you to a doctor.

301
00:22:13,350 --> 00:22:13,880
Let's go.

302
00:22:14,090 --> 00:22:15,310
I won't let you die.

303
00:22:15,330 --> 00:22:16,410
All must die!

304
00:22:16,490 --> 00:22:17,090
Let's go.

305
00:22:17,340 --> 00:22:18,750
Let's go, Zhang Qianjun.

306
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:21,150
Hang in there.

307
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:22,770
We'll find a doctor.

308
00:22:27,140 --> 00:22:28,000
Zhang Qianjun.

309
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:30,480
Mentor.

310
00:22:36,580 --> 00:22:37,100
Mentor.

311
00:22:38,980 --> 00:22:39,720
Mentor.

312
00:22:40,030 --> 00:22:40,830
Hang in there.

313
00:22:43,420 --> 00:22:45,180
Somebody, help!

314
00:22:45,780 --> 00:22:46,660
Please!

315
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:48,240
Please!

316
00:22:48,740 --> 00:22:49,270
Mentor.

317
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:27,460
So this is Bailejing.

318
00:24:39,110 --> 00:24:39,990
That's right.

319
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,700
This is the familiar feeling.

320
00:24:41,700 --> 00:24:43,830
This is what Bailejing should be like.

321
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:47,530
Shouldn't Bailejing

322
00:24:47,980 --> 00:24:48,980
be like what we saw just now?

323
00:24:48,980 --> 00:24:51,040
Why did it suddenly change into this?

324
00:24:52,660 --> 00:24:54,250
I have a bold guess.

325
00:24:54,610 --> 00:24:55,610
Is it possible

326
00:24:55,750 --> 00:24:57,180
that it's always been like this?

327
00:24:57,180 --> 00:24:58,960
It's just that the miasma here is toxic.

328
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:00,070
After outsiders come in,

329
00:25:00,070 --> 00:25:01,750
they will be mind-controlled
by the miasma,

330
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:03,310
and their behavior will become strange.

331
00:25:03,310 --> 00:25:05,250
Only by eating the local food

332
00:25:05,380 --> 00:25:06,780
can they return to normal

333
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:09,250
and see the true appearance of Bailejing.

334
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:12,030
No wonder.

335
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:13,090
Every time my mentor

336
00:25:13,090 --> 00:25:14,640
brought me to Bailejing,

337
00:25:14,810 --> 00:25:16,410
he made me eat terrible food.

338
00:25:17,330 --> 00:25:19,190
So that was the food of Bailejing.

339
00:25:19,660 --> 00:25:20,380
Little Taoist,

340
00:25:20,380 --> 00:25:21,290
you just remembered

341
00:25:21,290 --> 00:25:24,090
such an important message.
Aren't you a bit too...

342
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,830
Mentor, this outfit looks good on you.

343
00:25:29,790 --> 00:25:31,920
Mainly to avoid unnecessary trouble.

344
00:25:32,070 --> 00:25:34,110
It's better to do as the Romans do.

345
00:25:40,010 --> 00:25:40,610
He'll pay.

346
00:25:40,830 --> 00:25:41,400
Alright.

347
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:44,080
He'll pay.

348
00:25:44,750 --> 00:25:45,350
Alright.

349
00:25:47,670 --> 00:25:49,390
Sir, you haven't paid yet.

350
00:25:54,180 --> 00:25:54,980
How much is it, Ma'am?

351
00:25:54,980 --> 00:25:55,550
Twenty.

352
00:25:55,750 --> 00:25:56,570
Twenty.

353
00:25:59,510 --> 00:26:00,480
Alright, take a look at something else?

354
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:01,850
No need, thank you, Ma'am.

355
00:26:01,850 --> 00:26:02,510
Take care.

356
00:26:02,790 --> 00:26:05,520
Why did you make me pay
for the clothes you bought?

357
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:08,080
What's going on?

358
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:09,160
Why are you so happy?

359
00:26:09,160 --> 00:26:11,030
You weren't like this at all
when we were outside.

360
00:26:11,030 --> 00:26:11,750
Am I?

361
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:14,690
It's because of the food here.

362
00:26:14,900 --> 00:26:16,840
The food here makes people happy.

363
00:26:17,270 --> 00:26:19,800
Otherwise, why would it
be called Bailejing?

364
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:24,000
Fellow folks,

365
00:26:24,140 --> 00:26:25,640
last time we talked about

366
00:26:25,740 --> 00:26:27,810
the patron saint of our Bailejing,

367
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:29,340
Feikun Balu.

368
00:26:31,220 --> 00:26:34,300
This time, I'll tell you in detail.

369
00:26:34,830 --> 00:26:37,670
This Feikun Balu
is a god of the mountains.

370
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:39,910
He was born with divine power,

371
00:26:39,980 --> 00:26:42,680
controlling wind, rain,
thunder, and lightning.

372
00:26:42,680 --> 00:26:44,160
He is incredibly brave.

373
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:45,700
Twenty years ago,

374
00:26:46,140 --> 00:26:47,210
there was once

375
00:26:47,420 --> 00:26:49,250
a notorious Black Bone Demon

376
00:26:49,310 --> 00:26:50,970
running amok in the villages.

377
00:26:51,030 --> 00:26:53,360
The common people suffered unspeakably.

378
00:26:53,750 --> 00:26:54,480
At this time,

379
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:58,920
Feikun Balu rode the wind
with his divine weapon.

380
00:26:59,510 --> 00:27:01,170
Amidst the sky-shaking roar,

381
00:27:01,260 --> 00:27:03,390
he fought with the demon.

382
00:27:04,050 --> 00:27:06,250
When the divine weapon was brought out,

383
00:27:06,790 --> 00:27:09,810
the Black Bone Demon was no match for him.

384
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:12,930
It instantly turned into blue smoke
and dissipated.

385
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:15,160
From then on, Feikun Balu

386
00:27:15,420 --> 00:27:18,240
has protected our Bailejing day and night.

387
00:27:18,610 --> 00:27:22,660
No more demons
dare to set foot in our land.

388
00:27:22,750 --> 00:27:24,850
-Great!
-Great!

389
00:27:25,900 --> 00:27:27,610
Feikun Balu is just the chief.

390
00:27:28,310 --> 00:27:30,710
It seems that people here
treat him as a god.

391
00:27:30,770 --> 00:27:32,570
What's so good about being a god?

392
00:27:32,610 --> 00:27:34,070
It's better to be a mortal.

393
00:27:34,660 --> 00:27:36,090
Only when a person is dead

394
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:38,660
will they know how precious
it is to be alive.

395
00:27:39,510 --> 00:27:41,620
This divine weapon of Feikun Balu

396
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:43,540
fell right here in our Bailejing.

397
00:27:44,380 --> 00:27:46,430
But since it's a divine weapon,

398
00:27:46,530 --> 00:27:49,750
ordinary people definitely can't use it.

399
00:27:49,980 --> 00:27:52,070
Only when it meets its destined owner

400
00:27:52,770 --> 00:27:53,330
can it

401
00:27:53,590 --> 00:27:56,400
unleash its divine power.

402
00:27:56,420 --> 00:27:57,270
The priest is here!

403
00:27:57,270 --> 00:27:58,240
The priest is here.

404
00:27:58,240 --> 00:27:59,900
-The priest is here.
-The priest is here.

405
00:27:59,900 --> 00:28:01,340
-The priest is here.
-The priest is here.

406
00:28:01,340 --> 00:28:01,940
Let's go.

407
00:28:01,940 --> 00:28:02,900
-Let's go.
-Come on.

408
00:28:02,900 --> 00:28:03,590
Great.

409
00:28:03,740 --> 00:28:04,270
Let's go.

410
00:28:24,510 --> 00:28:26,310
Who is that sitting in the sedan?

411
00:28:27,110 --> 00:28:28,750
It's the High Priest of Bailejing.

412
00:28:28,750 --> 00:28:29,960
His name is Su Ya.

413
00:29:12,380 --> 00:29:13,780
Is that a person up there?

414
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:14,660
No.

415
00:29:15,550 --> 00:29:16,350
It's a corpse.

416
00:29:17,420 --> 00:29:18,530
I heard that the people here

417
00:29:18,530 --> 00:29:21,250
who want to rest in peace
after death or prosper in life

418
00:29:21,250 --> 00:29:22,510
all need his blessing.

419
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,480
Some people want to be high officials.

420
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:27,540
Some want to be wealthy businessmen.

421
00:29:28,010 --> 00:29:28,700
All of this

422
00:29:29,010 --> 00:29:30,740
relies on him pointing the way.

423
00:29:33,090 --> 00:29:36,420
The life and death of the people here
are all arranged by him.

424
00:30:03,570 --> 00:30:04,750
He can be saved.

425
00:30:09,640 --> 00:30:10,440
High Priest,

426
00:30:10,610 --> 00:30:11,590
is it true?

427
00:30:11,750 --> 00:30:13,810
Can my child really come back to life?

428
00:30:14,250 --> 00:30:15,630
Can he really save him?

429
00:30:15,670 --> 00:30:17,880
-Is he lying?
-Is it true?

430
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:57,770
He's really brought him back to life!
That's amazing!

431
00:30:57,770 --> 00:30:59,810
The priest is simply our true god!

432
00:30:59,830 --> 00:31:01,310
Thanks to him!

433
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:05,160
-Hail the priest!
-Hail the priest!

434
00:31:05,640 --> 00:31:07,660
-Hail the priest!
-Brilliant!

435
00:31:08,050 --> 00:31:09,900
-Brilliant!
-Hail the priest!

436
00:31:10,610 --> 00:31:13,180
-Hail the priest!
-He knows the magic

437
00:31:13,350 --> 00:31:14,750
and never claims credit.

438
00:31:14,790 --> 00:31:17,380
No wonder the people here
love him so much.

439
00:31:18,270 --> 00:31:19,970
Why don't we also go

440
00:31:20,140 --> 00:31:21,140
channel spirits

441
00:31:21,140 --> 00:31:22,940
and ask if there's any news
about the chief?

442
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:24,940
-Hail the priest!
-Hail the priest!

443
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:45,720
Who are you?

444
00:31:45,810 --> 00:31:46,480
Shh.

445
00:31:47,090 --> 00:31:48,020
Don't be afraid.

446
00:31:48,140 --> 00:31:49,660
I just want to ask one question.

447
00:31:49,660 --> 00:31:50,980
Do you know Zhang Qiling?

448
00:31:50,980 --> 00:31:51,660
Guards,

449
00:31:52,070 --> 00:31:53,570
arrest him!

450
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:26,480
Bofu (Thank you).

451
00:32:26,770 --> 00:32:29,100
It's my honor to protect you.

452
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:32,380
I have a matter to ask you.

453
00:32:32,510 --> 00:32:33,570
I wonder if we could

454
00:32:33,810 --> 00:32:34,810
speak in private.

455
00:32:34,830 --> 00:32:37,110
Honored guest, thank you.

456
00:32:37,510 --> 00:32:39,250
Please follow me inside.

457
00:32:58,560 --> 00:32:59,320
Commander,

458
00:32:59,460 --> 00:33:00,720
there is no road ahead.

459
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:02,350
Adjutant,

460
00:33:02,980 --> 00:33:04,270
in this situation,

461
00:33:04,380 --> 00:33:06,040
what do you think we should do?

462
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:08,200
There is only one road to Bailejing.

463
00:33:08,380 --> 00:33:09,510
We have to turn back.

464
00:33:11,380 --> 00:33:12,420
But I'm curious.

465
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:15,550
Why did you choose a dead-end road?

466
00:33:16,570 --> 00:33:17,750
Go to the front

467
00:33:17,770 --> 00:33:19,200
and set a fire.

468
00:33:19,350 --> 00:33:20,010
-Yes.
-Yes.

469
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:25,030
Do you know

470
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:28,550
what I came to Bailejing for?

471
00:33:30,090 --> 00:33:32,090
I'm not interested in what you want.

472
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:35,180
But I won't help you find
the Zhang family's chief.

473
00:33:36,140 --> 00:33:37,200
You are very smart.

474
00:33:38,450 --> 00:33:40,310
You will find Zhang Qiling for me,

475
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,500
because I will give you

476
00:33:43,310 --> 00:33:44,680
what you need.

477
00:33:45,220 --> 00:33:46,110
Even I don't know

478
00:33:46,110 --> 00:33:47,180
what I want.

479
00:33:47,790 --> 00:33:48,660
You do?

480
00:33:51,270 --> 00:33:52,570
Our eyes

481
00:33:53,530 --> 00:33:54,610
sit on the front of our faces,

482
00:33:54,610 --> 00:33:56,070
so they can look at others.

483
00:33:56,330 --> 00:33:58,130
That's why I can see you clearly,

484
00:33:58,750 --> 00:34:00,200
Zhang Haixia.

485
00:34:02,220 --> 00:34:03,380
However,

486
00:34:03,790 --> 00:34:05,680
eyes are also the most foolish.

487
00:34:06,070 --> 00:34:08,360
They often forget to look at themselves.

488
00:34:08,500 --> 00:34:09,670
Can you see

489
00:34:09,670 --> 00:34:11,330
how I'll eventually kill you?

490
00:34:15,650 --> 00:34:18,699
With all my elites around me,

491
00:34:19,130 --> 00:34:21,020
are you so sure you can kill me?

492
00:34:21,170 --> 00:34:22,170
How will you do it?

493
00:34:22,750 --> 00:34:23,540
Commander,

494
00:34:25,300 --> 00:34:26,400
you don't really think

495
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:27,300
I came here

496
00:34:27,300 --> 00:34:29,500
just because of your phone call, do you?

497
00:34:32,250 --> 00:34:33,230
Have you ever considered

498
00:34:33,230 --> 00:34:35,040
I might have planned all this

499
00:34:35,690 --> 00:34:37,889
just to be within half a meter of you now,

500
00:34:38,320 --> 00:34:40,320
so I could kill you with my own hands?

501
00:34:45,460 --> 00:34:47,590
Or maybe I don't even need
to do it myself,

502
00:34:47,590 --> 00:34:49,250
and they can kill you for me.

503
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:54,110
I like you very much.

504
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:58,440
It's just a pity

505
00:34:59,380 --> 00:35:01,300
that you are not Zhang Qiling.

506
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:03,730
You won't kill me.

507
00:35:05,110 --> 00:35:07,670
Because right now,

508
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:10,940
you are still in trouble and confusion.

509
00:35:12,510 --> 00:35:14,980
Are you in pain?

510
00:35:22,110 --> 00:35:25,310
You thought you had made your choice,

511
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:27,430
but when your mentor

512
00:35:27,460 --> 00:35:29,730
and Zhang Hailou appeared,

513
00:35:30,050 --> 00:35:33,400
you suddenly found yourself in pain again.

514
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:35,320
Do you know why?

515
00:35:36,340 --> 00:35:40,010
It's your past self haunting you.

516
00:35:43,050 --> 00:35:45,850
If you want me to kill
Zhang Haiqi and Zhang Hailou,

517
00:35:46,780 --> 00:35:49,030
I'll kill you right now.

518
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,480
There is no room for discussion on this.

519
00:35:56,050 --> 00:35:57,220
In that case,

520
00:35:58,070 --> 00:36:01,220
your ending will be terrible.

521
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:03,480
There is only death waiting for you.

522
00:36:04,710 --> 00:36:06,260
Do you know what it means?

523
00:36:07,170 --> 00:36:10,150
It will be your past self

524
00:36:11,050 --> 00:36:12,280
who kills you.

525
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:17,820
Actually, you've always been running away
from your past self.

526
00:36:18,340 --> 00:36:19,530
This is ridiculous.

527
00:36:20,210 --> 00:36:22,000
How can one hide from oneself?

528
00:36:22,130 --> 00:36:23,880
It's a pure waste of time.

529
00:36:24,550 --> 00:36:26,980
Remember, if you want to live,

530
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:30,710
you must defeat your past self.

531
00:36:34,530 --> 00:36:35,230
Look.

532
00:36:37,420 --> 00:36:38,420
There was no path,

533
00:36:39,170 --> 00:36:40,710
so make one yourself.

534
00:36:41,500 --> 00:36:42,820
To live in this world,

535
00:36:43,530 --> 00:36:44,660
there is no retreat—

536
00:36:45,190 --> 00:36:46,520
only forward progress.

537
00:36:51,110 --> 00:36:51,920
Commander.

538
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,000
I'm really glad

539
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:57,820
I answered your call back then.

540
00:37:02,300 --> 00:37:04,630
Are you going to help me
find Zhang Qiling?

541
00:37:13,380 --> 00:37:14,980
In my own way.

542
00:37:15,700 --> 00:37:16,390
Excellent!

543
00:37:17,130 --> 00:37:18,000
You three,

544
00:37:18,480 --> 00:37:19,610
follow the adjutant

545
00:37:19,860 --> 00:37:21,460
and execute his every order.

546
00:37:21,650 --> 00:37:23,650
Violators will be killed.

547
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:24,800
Yes.

548
00:37:31,940 --> 00:37:32,600
Commander,

549
00:37:33,340 --> 00:37:34,800
do you trust him that much?

550
00:37:35,460 --> 00:37:36,660
He's very dangerous.

551
00:37:36,690 --> 00:37:37,950
You are not dangerous,

552
00:37:38,070 --> 00:37:39,660
so you are useless.

553
00:37:45,340 --> 00:37:47,460
It's only fun if it's dangerous.

554
00:37:47,860 --> 00:37:49,340
This man

555
00:37:50,050 --> 00:37:51,010
won't stay.

556
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:53,840
But eventually, he'll come back.

557
00:37:54,650 --> 00:37:57,710
He will clear all obstacles for me,

558
00:37:58,880 --> 00:37:59,730
because

559
00:38:00,420 --> 00:38:03,090
he is my third adjutant.

560
00:38:07,010 --> 00:38:08,440
So once he finishes

561
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:10,730
doing all the dirty work for me,

